An Oklahoma-based, self-professed “bad runner” who abandoned expectations of what she should and shouldn’t do and starting running half-marathons. And then full marathons.

Moving our bodies is everything. We asked a handful of real-life Recreationalists what #DoingThings means to them — and how endorphins truly do make us all happier. See more of Katie @thekritch.

We’re on a mission to get the world moving. For us, fitness has never been about performance. We hike steep trails and hula hoop in the backyard simply because moving our bodies makes us happy. This is #DoingThings :wink:

That’s why we’re kicking the year off with a lineup of endorphin-worthy events, classes, and challenges inspired by the values we’ve been about since the beginning. Head to outdoorvoices.com to start #DoingThings

node.text:
Before Kristina Wagner (@kristinumber1) flew off to Tokyo, we asked the Olympic rower (and OV Boston Store Rec'spert!) to share a bird's eye view of her Olympic training plan. She's set to compete in the Women's Double Sculls finals with her boat partner Genevra Stone on Tuesday, July 28 at 8:18pm EST, so tune in if you can and give her a virtual shout!!

"Hey OV Fam! I'm Kristi, a part time OV Boston employee and full time US Rowing athlete headed to the Olympics in Tokyo! Making the Olympic team has been a lifelong dream of mine and I am so excited to race against the best in the world while representing my country. 2020 was a tough year for everyone, and my hope is that the Olympics can have a remarkable healing and transcendent power. I've always loved sports because of the magic they bring to the community; and believe strongly how important movement and #doingthings is for everyone, not just Olympic athletes. It is a special time to be a female athlete, and I feel so grateful to those who have come before me to blaze the trail and create the platform. I’m ready to jump in feet first, leave it all out on the water, and hopefully do my part to inspire the next generation. Here's a look at a day in my life before landing in Tokyo — lots of early morning practice, strength training, and OV team hangs, of course."
